<p>I have two string as below:</p>  <pre><code> ***ABCABCABCABCABC***  BBBTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTCCC </code></pre>  <p>I want to replace * position only from below string</p>  <p>So results could be:</p>  <pre><code> BBBABCABCABCABCABCCCC  BBBTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTCCC </code></pre>  <p>Is there any way to have elegant solution to using SQL Server function?</p>  <p>I already did it using below.</p>  <pre><code> DECLARE @Value1=PATINDEX('%[A,C,G,T]%', '***ABCABCABCABCABC***')  Select SUBSTRING('BBBTTTTTTTTTTTTTTTBBB', 0, @Value1)  .... </code></pre>  <p>But this is required many if else.</p>  <p>I want to know is there any simple way to replace it or not.</p>